SIMPLE: eavesdrop
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Eavesdrop
<hw>Eaves"drop`</hw> <pr>(⟦emac⟧vz"dr⟦ocr⟧p`)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Eaves</ets> + <ets>drop</ets>.]</ety> <def>To stand under the
eaves, near a window or at the door, of a house, to listen and learn
what is said within doors; hence, to listen secretly to what is said in
private.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To <qex>eavesdrop</qex> in disguises.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Eavesdrop</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Eavesdrop
<hw>Eaves"drop`</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The water which falls in drops
from the eaves of a house.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Eavesdropper</ent>⟦br⟧
